28/09/2004
WARSAW, Poland -- Bulgaria, Croatia, and Romania are on track to join the EU in 2007, Polish President Aleksander Kwasniewski told reporters Monday (27 September). 
During a joint press conference with Croatian counterpart Stipe Mesic, Kwasniewski promised to share his country's experience in "economic and judicial transformation, entry negotiations and the first taste of life in the EU". 
He added that Zagreb could complete its accession talks with the EU by 2007 despite its late start last June. 
He also promised to back Croatia's bid for NATO membership. 
Zagreb wants to join the Alliance in 2006. 
(Rzeczpospolita - 28/09/04; AFP - 27/09/04)
